# Testing rules

## General

- Every new handler MUST have unit tests
- Every new validator MUST have unit tests
- Every new API endpoint MUST have an integration test
- Every correctness property (P1–P41) MUST have a property-based test
- Do not duplicate unit-test coverage with property tests for the same narrow examples
- Prefer **test data builders** or shared factories over copy-pasted object graphs; keep tests readable.
- **Time:** inject **`TimeProvider`** / clock abstractions for logic tied to “now”; avoid flaky tests that depend on real wall-clock unless testing integration with the system clock.
- **Flaky tests:** fix root cause; if temporarily quarantined, track owner and deadline — do not normalize red CI.

## FsCheck (C#)

- Library: FsCheck.Xunit
- Minimum: `[Property(MaxTest = 100)]` for all properties
- Security/access-control (P10, P24, P31, P37, P38, P39): `[Property(MaxTest = 500)]`
- Tag format (required): `// Feature: online-healthcare-platform, Property {N}: {property_title}`
- Custom generators: `tests/HealthPlatform.Tests.Properties/Arbitraries/`

## Hypothesis (Python)

- Library: Hypothesis with pytest
- Minimum: `@settings(max_examples=100)`
- Tag: `# Feature: online-healthcare-platform, Property {N}: {property_title}`
- P14: same input → same output across multiple calls in one test run

## Unit tests (C#)

- Framework: xUnit + Moq
- Naming: `{HandlerName}Tests`, `{ValidatorName}Tests`, `{DomainClass}Tests`
- Arrange / Act / Assert with blank-line separation; no shared mutable state between methods
- Mock all Application interfaces — never real Infrastructure in unit tests

## Integration tests

- Framework: xUnit + `WebApplicationFactory<Program>` + Testcontainers (PostgreSQL, Redis, Elasticsearch, MongoDB)
- Flows: patient registration → appointment → telemedicine → prescription → order → adherence
- Payment gateways: sandbox only
- Health record access matrix: all role combinations (allowed and denied)
- Audit log completeness verified

## Performance targets (document in test project README)

- Appointment booking: 1,000 concurrent bookings without slot collision
- Telemedicine RTC token: < 3 seconds
- Notifications: 10,000/minute
- Doctor search with geo-filter: < 500ms

