# Data layer rules

## PostgreSQL — system of record

- ACID for: payments, appointment booking, slot holds, prescription dispensing
- `AuditLog`: append-only; never UPDATE/DELETE paths
- Soft deletes: `IsDeleted` + `DeletedAt`; global EF filter excludes soft-deleted
- Never hard-delete patients — GDPR via anonymization

## MongoDB — unstructured / flexible

Collections: HealthRecordEntry, MoodLog, TherapySession summaries, AntenatalRecord entries, LabResult annotations. Typed models only — never `BsonDocument` in application logic.

## Redis — cache + coordination

- Slot hold: `slot:{slotId}:hold`, TTL 600s, SET NX for exclusivity
- Never primary data store — cache and ephemeral coordination only

## Elasticsearch — search only

Geo-distance for proximity. Read-only, eventually consistent — not for transactional queries. Index sync via domain events or Hangfire only.

## Cross-database consistency

PostgreSQL is system of record; MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Redis are derived. Never update MongoDB or Elasticsearch directly from a request handler — domain events + outbox.

